27:14                                   _s_t_r_á_n_k_a_]
sebelitost, iluze, pretvarka a silna slo
Jednou jsem tak zkousela napsat motivacni dopis na jednu pozici nakonec jsem
ho neposlaala, protoze obsahoval hodne chyb a chtela jsem ho nechat
zkontrolovat od pratel a mezitim mi vypadl internet.
Nicmene jsem ho pouzila mnohokrat pri sebereflexi toho co jsem v zivote
dokazala nebo nedokazala a neni toho mnoho.
Problem je, ze v mem veku uz bych mela neco dokazat nebo mit nejaky smer.
Nemam zadnou budoucnost, nemam partnera a nejjsem ani atraktivni kocka nebo
skvela kucharka abych sve profesni nedostatky dohnala jinde. Jsem jen moc
uprimna, premysliva a trpim lehkou formou hranicni poruchy osobnosti takze to
ze nevim kdo jsem a co chci a pak se pro to casto trapim me asi bude provazet
po zbytek zivota. Rodina mi porad vtloukala do hlavy ze jsem nadprumerne
inteligentni a ve stejnou dobu se mi nedarilo nebo se mi posmivali spoluzaci.
Mela sem bulimii kvuli depkam ze vzhledu ale ten uz neresim protoze mam nejak
pocit ze dietareni mi sezralo nnejvic casu ktery jsem prave mela travit
stanovovanim zivotniho smeru a cilu...... Nemuzu delat prace co by me bavily
jako servirku nebo barmanku protoze nemam zadnou praxi ackoli mam hotelovku a
neumim proste lidem lhat a tu praxi si vymyslet jako to dela mnoho lidi.....
nesnasim psani motivacnich dopisu a zivotopisu protoze krome toho ze porad
bloudim v kruhu a narazim do zdi tam vlastne nemam co psat... :/ ... vybrala
sem si praci misto vzdelani tenkrat po maturite a sla jsem delat sekretarku za
ctrnact tisic mesicne v Praze na tri roky... pak mi to bylo malo chtela sem
vzdelani ale vybrala sem si spatnou vejsku ktra mi nic nerika
udelala sem si pruvodcovskej kurz ale neumim tak dobre dejepis
chtela bych pracovat mezi lidma ne v kancelari ale nechci delat celej zivot
servirku v restauraci co ani nekasiruje a jen uklizi vetsinu casu spinavy
nadobi nebo prodavacku v supermarketu za par susni.... sebevedomi v projevu mi
znacne chybi i kdyz na zelandu se mi parkrat projevilo jenze pro me jsou to
hodnotove proste bezcenny nepravdivy zvasty a lzi a ja nechci byt umelej
superhrdina co dokaze vsechno vsude byl vsechno zna a sezral pulku moudrosti
sveta
pak se ale divim, ze mi pratele rikaji proboha tohle nikam neposilej

Dear Megan,

I am just wondering, if you are still looking for the receptionist. I have
graduated in 2009 in hospitality and tourism in the Czech republic. Than i had
a choice between very good hotel receptionist in the Prague city center (hotel
Diplomat Praha) and secretary job. Unfortunatelly i have chosen the second
choice, because it meant more certainty.

Than after three years i had the passion to come back to my tourism area and
made the tour guide course, than have worked like a waitress, shop asistant,
in promotion, call centres and because it was the bad time for looking for
proper job (economical crise) i have bought the working holiday visa to
improve my English to the fluent level.

Meanwhile i got a seasonal job as a flight attendant. This job was great, but
just for few months a year and I would love to work all the year no just a
half of it and than having no future. In adition I noticed, that this kind of
job is quite unhealthy for whole human body.

I am fully enjoing people and all kind of customer services so I dont want to
go back to the separate office or trade area which cheating of people with
certainly best deal of their life, in addition I particularly still regret my
previous mistake, when I was declined the receptionist job back in Prague.

After my arrival to New Zealand i didnt start my traveling and fruitpicking as
many people from my country did. I took a nonpaid internship in the language
institut (NEW ZEALAND INSTITUTE OF STUDIES) for two months (I was supposed to
work three, but fees in Auckland was very hight and I needed to take some paid
job instead). Despite I was rejected my practice little bit earlier, I have
studied IELTS preparations there like an exchange, to get more information,
how to start living in New Zealand permanently. I havent passed the official
IELTS due to the hight price of thist test, but at least I have passed the
exam for business students in approximate band 6.5.

Except my educational reasons I have got a lot of working experiences in New
Zealand industry and customer service. I was receptionist and student asistent
in everyday situations and meanwhile I was working with school database,
banding new study materials, taking payments for books and printing credit and
helping to European marketing manager. I loved daily contact with students and
being usefull and making students happy. In the end of my internship I also
improved my qualification with barista training.

From time to time I was working for catering agency Providore on temporary
events like weddings and worked weekends in busy coffee in Orakei as well.

January is my third month in New Zealand, I have realised, that imigration is
very hard and expensive process (but still will keep trying) so I decided to
get the great career opportunity and move from this big city (which is
unfortunatelly very quiet in summer season for working challenges) and go to
discover the area of Bay of Plenty.

I am very happy to read about your vacancy and believe, that I am the right
person for your possition, based of my passion for people and brilliant
customer service, my quicklearning skills, previous experiences in various
tourism positions and will to work hard on every rooster shifts (night, all
day, weekend or holiday shifts doesnt matter). I love learning new skills,
speaking with people and helping others.
